j2782529035
g.text: You've been... I'm not the easiest man to get to know. You've put up with me dodging.

g.title: j829782175
g.text: To be fair, I've been doing the same thing to you about what made me, me. Duviri, and all...

g.title: j150570244
g.text: Talking about the dark parts of our past isn't easy or fun for anybody.

g.title: j1427702717
g.text: Yeah. About time you man up, cowboy.

g.title: j2767721283
g.text: Well, the point is, you've been waiting around trying to get the whole story out of me -

g.title: j4056074466
g.text: And immediately? I've changed my mind.

g.title: j1156666540
g.text: how I got here, how I got like this,

g.title: j4128474556
g.text: the rest of the story about this sword,

g.title: j125307758
g.text: and all the rest of this ugly mess...

g.title: j625245804
g.text: Pour yourself a cup of tea.

g.title: j333695737
g.text: Actually, a beer would be best.

g.title: j2471379567
g.text: I'll try to make this brief. Sol knows I don't want to dwell on this shit any more than I need to.

g.title: j4268206184
g.text: Take the time you need. I'm here.

g.title: j2912779827
g.text: I told you why I left the Britannic Army. I never told you why I joined.

g.title: j351180749
g.text: When I was a lad, there was a childhood friend a few years above Eleanor and I in school. Lived a few doors up the street.

g.title: j2542246758
g.text: This skana of mine that you've asked after.

g.title: j927390004
g.text: The bandana I keep on my blade?

g.title: j3322747461
g.text: Eleanor told me her half of the Christopher story already.

g.title: j2872098010
g.text: Name was Christopher. He was always sticking up for the kids in the neighborhood who needed it.

g.title: j935263084
g.text: I told you how I got it. Entrati running me through with it. Not long after he turned me into this...

g.title: j3727545067
g.text: I got it when Entrati ran me through with it. Not long after he turned me into this...

g.title: j1808446780
g.text: Christopher got it for me... as a gift for joining the Crimson Watch.

g.title: j1936370271
g.text: There was... an old friend of mine, way back in the day.

g.title: j3879410016
g.text: He was bigger, tougher - smarter. One of those blokes you'd want to push in front of a lorry if he wasn't so damned NICE all the time.

g.title: j139908051
g.text: He was planning on giving it to me the night I got there.

g.title: j2590580756
g.text: I... can't thank you enough for being there for her. For finally being someone who might get her past what she lost on that terrible day.

g.title: j4063840726
g.text: She... lost a lot more than me, that day.

g.title: j4028199645
g.text: In short? I bloody wanted to BE him, growing up. Followed in his footsteps any way I could.

g.title: j1143977465
g.text: But I dodged when you asked me about the bandana.

g.title: j2832456091
g.text: But it's not the blade that's important to me. It's the bandana.

g.title: j2800260242
g.text: You. You're just YOU. Inside. Where it counts.

g.title: j2001192569
g.text: It was waiting for me... instead of him.

g.title: j70085842
g.text: Christopher? Eleanor told me some of it.

g.title: j3705256016
g.text: It was meant to be a gift. He never got to deliver it to me.

g.title: j865030810
g.text: She makes it sound like you both lost someone special.

g.title: j4104522561
g.text: But it sounds like you both lost someone that meant a lot to you.

g.title: j2027569647
g.text: I was lucky enough to call my idol my best friend.

g.title: j3594653001
g.text: I... will never adjust to that.

g.title: j651390891
g.text: Thanks. I need to remember that.

g.title: j2553936140
g.text: What happened to him isn't your fault, Arthur.

g.title: j3984631062
g.text: War takes the best of us away.

g.title: j494208529
g.text: He was a dear friend and I looked up to him like a big brother. I idolized him.

g.title: j3043948041
g.text: So when he went off and joined His Majesty's Service, as soon as he was of age? I was biting at the bit, waiting until I was old enough to do the same.

g.title: j2412567942
g.text: Well. That's how I got the blade.

g.title: j951845806
g.text: I know. But it is my duty to carry on.

g.title: j1855600863
g.text: Christopher represented everything I wanted to be in this world - noble, heroic, self-sacrificing.

g.title: j411485570
g.text: Never mind the fact that he...

g.title: j2947006609
g.text: Thank you for being there for her. For helping her heal.

g.title: j2859696185
g.text: He was bigger, tougher - smarter. One of those blokes you'd want to push in front of a lorry if he wasn't so damned NICE all the time.

g.title: j2963608438
g.text: Look, Drifter... This part isn't my story to tell. It's Eleanor's. But I'll say this much. When Christopher went off to war?

g.title: j2943442480
g.text: But sometimes, an old ghost is a welcome one.

g.title: j214748171
g.text: You've helped me heal a lot of that old pain, by being here for me.

g.title: j898283341
g.text: So when he went off and joined His Majesty's Service, as soon as he was of age? I was biting at the bit, waiting until I was old enough to do the same.

g.title: j3742183060
g.text: I wasn't the only one upset to see him go.

g.title: j3563609063
g.text: They remind us of why we're still here. Who we were before.

g.title: j2516920383
g.text: Imagine poor Eleanor, having to watch her fianc and her twin brother go off to war.

g.title: j382712707
g.text: He must have really meant a lot to you.

g.title: j4090315514
g.text: She never trusted authority. But after what happened to the two of us? She never would again.

g.title: j1022788035
g.text: Christopher had pulled some strings. Lined it up so that I'd be in the same regiment as him. 3rd Battalion, Crimson Watch.

g.title: j3526406320
g.text: And who we're still fighting for.

g.title: j2951631230
g.text: I can't say I blame her.

g.title: j2137487597
g.text: But one week before I got out there... there was an incident. Roadside bomb.

g.title: j2387965275
g.text: I... never really had anyone to fight for. Not until recently. One reason they call me 'Drifter.'

g.title: j2559247139
g.text: I've run out of imaginary beers to drink. I kind of need a real one, now.

g.title: j4239617453
g.text: And like so many good men and women? Like so many good soldiers?

g.title: j1758957007
g.text: I can't tell which one of us has had it worse. Both. Neither.

g.title: j2220888507
g.text: You haven't had it much better than me, have you, though?

g.title: j4139494359
g.text: He became just another number on somebody's sheet.

g.title: j4261925348
g.text: Creations of war, just in different ways. We've both lost a lot in our lives.

g.title: j382752455
g.text: But I was still a naive fool. And I, like an idiot, was all too eager to pick up the mantle he left behind...

g.title: j1299254043
g.text: No one wins in war. No one.

g.title: j3425115850
g.text: I... yeah. But. That was... heavy. Drinks? You and me? Then we go find a quiet place to talk in person?

g.title: j2992158718
g.text: We've both lost things, yes. But look at how much we've found. Friends. Family. Each other.

g.title: j2392715776
g.text: You lost... one guy? All this was about *one* guy? I was expecting something way more dramatic.

g.title: j2603235129
g.text: Look at what we've been able to do here.

g.title: j3410699072
g.text: Love, nothing would make me happier right now.

g.title: j2904979716
g.text: You're right. Enough of this moody shit for one day.
